						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is fragmentary and is built in at the right end. It records a gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land for offerings and for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva at Tirukkarugāvūr by one <hi rend="bold">[Śē]ndaṉ Tāḻi</hi> after purchasing the same from three individual owners.</p>						

						</summary>
